<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!--Head-->
<%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/head`, { SEO:false, Title:`Vrbo Partner-entry funnel redesign`,
  text:'Reducing early-stage drop-off in mobile funnels with incomplete data', pageURL:'bq_b2c_vrbo/',
  thumbnailImgURL: 'vickywang.svg' }) %>
<!--Head-->

<body class="">


  <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/header_back`, {
  tab1:'Problem',
  tab1_data_link:'problem', 

  tab2:'Insights',
  tab2_data_link:'insights',

  tab3:'Design',
  tab3_data_link:'design',

  tab4_display:'displayTab',
  tab4:'Impact',
  tab4_data_link:'impact',
  }) %>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <div class="blankHXS"></div>
    <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
      <div class="Grid-cell">
        <div class="element">
          <img class="widthXXS" src="../../logos/bq.svg" alt="Logo">

            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_about_bq`) %>

          <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

          <h1 class="titleCaseStudy">Converting High-Intent Partner Traffic Under In-App Constraints (Vrbo)</h1>
          <h3 class="fontWeight300">Reducing early-stage drop-off in mobile funnels with incomplete data</h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">
      <div class="Grid-cell">
        <div class="element">
          <h5><span class="fontWeight400">Role: </span>Lead UX for partner-entry mobile web flow</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class=" Grid-cell">
        <div class="element">
          <h5><span class="fontWeight400">Scope: </span>Partner-entry funnel redesign · Mobile web · Consumer booking flow</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class=" Grid-cell">
        <div class="element">
          <h5><span class="fontWeight400">Stakeholders: </span>Product Design, CTO, engineering, QA, partner-facing teams</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section id="problem" data-nav="problem">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Context & Problem',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
          <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>

            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Context</h1>

            <h4>Vrbo brought <span class="fontWeight400">high-intent, mobile-heavy traffic</span> into BabyQuip’s embedded mobile web experience, where users entered mid-journey inside a constrained in-app browser.</h4>
            <!-- <h4>BabyQuip’s gear-first browsing flow supported partner discovery, but the provider-based backend meant pricing and availability were not reliable until QP selection. Vrbo exposed this mismatch because high-intent users entered through a constrained mobile webview with little context. I redesigned the flow to reduce false progress, make provider commitment clearer, and simplify the path from shopping to checkout, while identifying the deeper unresolved marketplace tension between gear-first browsing and provider-first fulfillment.
            </h4> -->

            <div class="spacingMedium"></div>


            <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Problem</h1>
            <h4>The experience encouraged <span class="fontWeight400">item-first browsing</span> even though <span class="fontWeight400">price, availability, and fulfillment still depended on provider selection</span>, allowing users to build carts that felt complete before a bookable order actually existed.
            </h4>

          </div>
          <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
        </div>
      </div>



    </div>
  </section>



  <section id="insights" data-nav="insights">

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Insights',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
          <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
        </div>
      </div>



      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Where the funnel broke</h1>
            <h4>GA4 and Hotjar showed that Vrbo users were not primarily failing at checkout. They were dropping earlier, before the flow established enough context, trust, and provider commitment.</h4>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">GA4 funnel comparison</h1>
            <h4>To avoid comparing partner traffic against desktop-heavy baseline traffic, I separated the analysis into two views.</h4>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Mobile comparison: Vrbo vs. non-Vrbo</h4>


            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="ga4_vrbo_nonvrbo_traffic.png" alt="Vrbo mobile vs non-Vrbo mobile">


            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5 class="fontWeight400">How did Vrbo mobile compare with non-Vrbo mobile traffic?</h5>

              <h6>· Compared with non-Vrbo mobile traffic, Vrbo mobile users dropped earlier in the funnel, while later-stage completion remained strong.</h6>

              <h6>· The biggest issue was not checkout, but early-stage progression from entry/shopping toward provider commitment.
              </h6>


            </div>


          </div>

        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400"> Vrbo comparison: mobile vs. web</h4>

            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="ga4_mobile_vs_web_traffic.png" alt="Vrbo mobile vs Vrbo web">



            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5 class="fontWeight400">Is Vrbo mainly a mobile/in-app browser problem?</h5>

              <h6>· Vrbo traffic was primarily mobile web, making the embedded in-app browser the highest-priority surface to fix.</h6>

              <h6>· Vrbo mobile performed worse at early stages than Vrbo web, making embedded mobile web the priority.</h6>


            </div>



          </div>
        </div>


      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="textItalic fontWeight100 GreyBg400 GreyBg100 border-radius paddingXS">💡 Key insight: users dropped before context, trust, and provider commitment were established.</h4>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>



    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">


      <div class="spacingXLarge"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">What the data meant in the experience</h1>
            <h4>The funnel data pointed to an early-stage problem, but the product experience revealed four distinct breakdowns:</h4>
            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· <span class="fontWeight400">Entry:</span> unclear context and trust (“Where am I?”)</h5>
              <h5>· <span class="fontWeight400">Shopping:</span> misleading progress (“This feels like a real cart”)</h5>
              <h5>· <span class="fontWeight400">Commitment:</span> missing decision moment (“I haven’t actually chosen a provider”)</h5>
              <h5>· <span class="fontWeight400">Pre-checkout:</span> redundant flow (“Why am I doing this again?”)</h5>
              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingXLarge"></div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">A. Entry confusion </h4>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· Multiple overlays created a fragmented entry experience</h5>
              <h5>· Missing loading state made the app feel unresponsive</h5>
              <h5>· Unclear ownership between Vrbo and BabyQuip reduced trust</h5>

              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_pre_entry.png" alt="">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">


        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">B. Shopping created false progress in a provider-dependent marketplace</h4>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· Users added items before selecting a provider, even though pricing and availability depended on it</h5>
              <h5>· The cart appeared complete while a required step (provider selection) was still missing</h5>
              <h5>· Placeholder pricing and generic item details reinforced a false sense of certainty</h5>
              <h5>· The flow did not clearly transition users from browsing to provider selection</h5>

              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_shop_placeholder_items.png" alt="">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">


        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">C. Provider selection gap </h4>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· Add-to-cart used success feedback, making an incomplete step feel like completion</h5>
              <h5>· CTA hierarchy favored continued browsing over provider selection</h5>
              <h5>· Provider selection was available but not treated as the next required step</h5>

              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_provider_selection.png" alt="">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">


        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">D. Pre-checkout chaos</h4>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· Repeated states across order summary and add-ons created unnecessary loops</h5>
              <h5>· Competing CTAs made it unclear whether to continue or checkout</h5>
              <h5>· The flow resembled checkout before users were actually ready to complete</h5>

            </div>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_precheckout.png" alt="">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>


    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

  </section>
  <section id="design" data-nav="design">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Design',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>

            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">
                  <h1 class="fontWeight400">Design principles</h1>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="fontWeight400">1. Clarify context before action</h4>
                    <h5>Users need to understand where they are, what carried over from Vrbo, and what can be trusted before they act.</h5>

                    <h4 class="fontWeight400">2. Make commitment visible at the right moment</h4>
                    <h5>Shift the flow from endless exploration toward clear provider selection and checkout progression.</h5>
                    <h4 class="fontWeight400">3. Remove false progress and repeated decisions</h4>
                    <h5>Avoid screens and states that look complete before pricing, availability, or fulfillment are actually resolved.</h5>
                  </div>

                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="spacingXLarge"></div>

            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">
                  <h1 class="fontWeight400">Solutions</h1>
                  <h4>Because pricing and availability could not be finalized before provider selection, the redesign made that uncertainty visible through contextual messaging instead of letting the UI imply false certainty.</h4>
                </div>

              </div>
              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">1. <span class="fontWeight500">Entry:</span> clarify context on arrival (Vrbo-specific)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <h4>· Reduce system interruptions at entry</h4>
                      <h4>· Surface trip details early so users understand what they are booking against</h4>
                      <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
                    </div>
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_pre_entry.png" alt="">
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">2.<span class="fontWeight500">Shopping:</span> reduce false progress before provider selection (Vrbo-specific)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <h4>· De-emphasize placeholder pricing and incomplete item certainty</h4>
                      <h4>· Reframe add-to-cart as a transition, not a completion moment</h4>


                      <h4>· Guide users from browsing toward provider selection as the next required step</h4>
                      <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
                    </div>
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_shopping.png" alt="">

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">3. <span class="fontWeight500">Commitment:</span> make provider selection explicit at the right moment (cross-platform)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <h4>· Make provider selection visible and necessary</h4>
                      <h4>· Reduce dead-end cart states before fulfillment is confirmed</h4>
                      <h4>· Align user actions with provider-based marketplace logic</h4>
                      <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
                    </div>
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_select_provider.png" alt="">

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">4. <span class="fontWeight500">Pre-Checkout:</span> remove redundant decision states (cross-platform)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <h4>· Remove repeated decision states across cart, add-ons, and summary</h4>
                      <h4>· Make checkout the dominant action once users are ready to commit</h4>
                      <h4>· Consolidate add-ons, order summary, and checkout into one continuous path</h4>

                    </div>

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_pre_checkout.png" alt="">

                    <h4><span class="fontWeight400">Before:</span> fragmented flow with repeated decision states before checkout</h4>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_pre_checkout.png" alt="">

                    <h4><span class="fontWeight400">After:</span> one continuous path from add-ons to checkout</h4>

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

  </section>

  <section id="impact" data-nav="impact">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Impact',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Expected product impact</h1>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h4>· Reduce early-stage drop-off by making provider commitment explicit earlier in the flow.</h4>
              <h4>· Increase progression from shopping into provider selection.</h4>
              <h4>· Maintain or improve completion after item selection by reducing redundant decision loops</h4>
              <h4>· Established reusable pattern for partner traffic</h4>

              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Measurement plan</h1>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h4>· Measure post-launch funnel progression across entry -> shopping -> provider selection -> checkout, with special attention to early-stage lift on mobile Vrbo traffic.</h4>

              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Trade-offs</h1>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h4>· <span class="fontWeight400">Did not resolve the provider-first vs gear-first model tension</span>: users still browse before fulfillment is fully known</h4>
              <h4>· <span class="fontWeight400">Placeholder item logic remains</span>: pricing and availability still become reliable only after provider selection</h4>
              <h4>· Did not enable provider selection without items (explored but not shipped)</h4>
              <h4>· Limited by embedded webview + tracking gaps</h4>

              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">What this did not solve</h1>

            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Future direction:</h4>
            <h5>Longer term, the better structural fix is a dual-entry model that supports both browse-first and provider-first journeys.</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_dual-entry_model.png" alt="Provider selection available before item selection">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>
  <!-- Case study ends -->
  <div class="blankHS"></div>
  <!-- Shared across the platform -->
  <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/footer`) %>
  <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/imgModal`) %>


